  "def": "Measuring where a program spends time/memory to find optimisation targets empirically.",
  "problem": "Optimise based on evidence, not guesses, by locating actual hot spots.",
  "mechanism": "Sampling profilers periodically capture stacks (low overhead); instrumenting profilers count every call (precise, higher overhead); both attribute cost to code.",
